race.comment: The $160,000 Listed Tattersall's Classic. MIDNIGHT IN TOKYO (5) returned in fine fashion with a second in the Listed Keith Noud and loves this course and distance not missing a drum in five attempts. Will have come on with that run now in the locker and looks very tough to hold out. ZASZOU (2) strips fitter second-up from the break and did get up to Group 1 level when last in work. Bright prospects. LONHRO'S QUEEN (8) is a bit hit or miss but has saluted on all going and draws favourably in the inside alley. Capable of a strong showing if she brings her A-game. The well-related SUNSET DREAMING (9) (half to G1 winner Benedetta) gets the reliable Gollan/Jones combination and looks one for the multiples. EL MORZILLO (3) best of the rest despite the sticky draw.
